WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.420
So which is the real Dance of Death?

00:00:02.640 --> 00:00:04.840
Here the interpretations split, and both

00:00:04.840 --> 00:00:05.400
have weight.

00:00:05.740 --> 00:00:07.940
The traditional reading is the gentle one.

00:00:08.180 --> 00:00:10.980
This is a memento mori: Death comes for

00:00:10.980 --> 00:00:13.260
everyone, pope and ploughman alike, so

00:00:13.260 --> 00:00:15.380
prepare your soul, because status counts

00:00:15.380 --> 00:00:16.760
for nothing in the end.

00:00:16.960 --> 00:00:19.920
Pious, universal, and perfectly at home in

00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:20.720
a prayer book.

00:00:21.020 --> 00:00:23.340
But notice who Death visits, and how.

00:00:23.720 --> 00:00:26.240
He marches the pope, the cardinal, the

00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:28.780
bishop, the abbot, the emperor and the

00:00:28.780 --> 00:00:31.000
king to the front of the procession, and

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:33.380
he saves his cruelest jokes for exactly

00:00:33.380 --> 00:00:35.620
the people who claimed to stand above the

00:00:35.620 --> 00:00:37.000
crowd — and closest to God.

00:00:38.040 --> 00:00:40.480
Read that way, the series stops being a

00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:42.980
soft reminder of mortality and becomes a

00:00:42.980 --> 00:00:45.080
reckoning: Death as the one honest

00:00:45.080 --> 00:00:47.800
official who cannot be bribed, flattered,

00:00:48.020 --> 00:00:48.960
or outranked.

00:00:49.220 --> 00:00:50.700
And yet — and this is where it

00:00:50.700 --> 00:00:53.280
stays honest — Holbein doesn't simply hate

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:53.880
the Church.

00:00:54.120 --> 00:00:56.000
Look closely and you'll find that the

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.060
humble preacher and the parish priest

00:00:58.060 --> 00:01:00.980
escape his sarcasm entirely; they're shown

00:01:00.980 --> 00:01:02.420
in sympathy with the poor.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.000
His scorn isn't aimed at faith.

00:01:05.380 --> 00:01:06.300
It's aimed at power.
